Source: Country Work
Author: CARR
Vol / Page: 44
Edition:
Quote: [The flax fibre] is carted ... to the drying green, generally called the `paddock', where it is spread out to dry and bleach. ... It is [then] taken in hand by the `scutcher', who feeds it into a revolving drum ... which beats the refuse out.
